# How to Make Sure All Stories Exist in V4\
\
V4 assembly requires **story atoms** for each (persona, topic, role, engine, length) when it injects a micro-story into a slot. If any required combination is missing, assembly fails with "No story_atoms found for this combination."\
\
---\
\
## 1. Where stories must live\
\
**Root:** 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/data/story_bank/story_atoms/
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
\
**Layout:**\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f7 \cf0 text\
story_atoms/\
  \{persona\}/           e.g. gen_z_la, gen_z_professionals, healthcare_burnout\
    \{topic\}/           e.g. anxiety, burnout, grief, stress\
      \{engine\}/        from topic_engine_bindings.yaml (e.g. avoidance_trap, legacy, false_alarm)\
        \{role\}/        recognition | mechanism_proof | turning_point | embodiment\
          micro/       length (V4 uses micro)\
            *.txt      one file per variant (e.g. v01.txt, v02.txt)\
            *_meta.yaml  optional; status: confirmed | provisional\
            metadata.yaml  optional folder-level defaults
\f0 \
\
**Required roles (all four):** 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 recognition
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 mechanism_proof
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 turning_point
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 embodiment
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
\
**Engines per topic:** Defined in 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 phoenix_v4/planning/topic_engine_bindings.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 . Each topic lists 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 allowed_engines
\f0\fs32 \cb7 . At least one engine for that topic must have content under 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 story_atoms/\{persona\}/\{topic\}/\{engine\}/\{role\}/micro/
\f0\fs32 \cb7 .\
\
**Minimum variants:** For reliable assembly and plan-time coverage, aim for **\uc0\u8805  5 variants per role** (e.g. 5+ 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 .txt
\f0\fs32 \cb7  files in that role\'92s 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 micro/
\f0\fs32 \cb7  folder). Format policy can require more (e.g. 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 standard_book
\f0\fs32 \cb7  in 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 phoenix_v4/policy/format_story_quality.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 : 10 recognition, 10 mechanism_proof, 6 turning_point, 6 embodiment for confirmed-only).\
\
---\
\
## 2. Check what\'92s missing\
\
### A. Topic readiness (one persona \'d7 topic)\
\

\f7 bash\
python3 phoenix_v4/ci/check_topic_readiness.py <topic> <persona> --verbose\
# Example:\
python3 phoenix_v4/ci/check_topic_readiness.py anxiety gen_z_la --min-level RELEASE_READY --verbose
\f0 \
\
Use 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 --min-level RELEASE_READY
\f0\fs32 \cb7  to enforce enough atoms for release. Output shows whether story_atoms coverage is sufficient.\
\
### B. Full coverage report (all personas \'d7 topics)\
\

\f7 bash\
python3 phoenix_v4/ci/story_atoms_coverage_report.py --out artifacts/story_atoms_coverage.json
\f0 \
\
Then inspect 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 artifacts/story_atoms_coverage.json
\f0\fs32 \cb7 : each 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 persona::topic
\f0\fs32 \cb7  has 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 status
\f0\fs32 \cb7  (READY | PARTIAL | MISSING) and 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 missing
\f0\fs32 \cb7  path hints. **READY** = all required roles have \uc0\u8805  5 variants for at least one allowed engine.\
\
### C. Plan-time coverage (when compiling a plan)\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f7\fs28 \cf0 \cb8 compile_format_plan
\f0\fs32 \cb7  uses 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 phoenix_v4/planning/coverage_checker.py
\f0\fs32 \cb7  and 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 phoenix_v4/policy/format_story_quality.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 . If you don\'92t use 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 --allow-coverage-gaps
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , it will raise when counts are below the format\'92s 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 min_atoms_per_role
\f0\fs32 \cb7  (and when 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 V4_STRICT
\f0\fs32 \cb7  is on). So running a plan compile for a given (format, persona, topic) and seeing no coverage error is another \'93stories exist\'94 check.\
\
