\
## 3. Fix missing stories\
\
### Option A: Add story atoms\
\
1. Create the directory for the missing (persona, topic, engine, role):\
   
\f7 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb7 text\
   SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/data/story_bank/story_atoms/\{persona\}/\{topic\}/\{engine\}/\{role\}/micro/
\f0 \
2. Add 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 .txt
\f0\fs32 \cb7  files (one per variant, e.g. 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 v01.txt
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 v02.txt
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , \'85).\
3. Optionally add 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 v01_meta.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 v02_meta.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , \'85 with 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 status: confirmed
\f0\fs32 \cb7  or 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 status: provisional
\f0\fs32 \cb7 .\
4. Ensure the **engine** is in 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 topic_engine_bindings.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7  under that topic\'92s 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 allowed_engines
\f0\fs32 \cb7 .\
\
Use your normal authoring or generation pipeline (e.g. prompt packs from 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 phoenix_v4/agent/system_atom_packs.py
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , or manual authoring) to create the content.\
\
### Option B: Persona fallback (temporary)\
\
In 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 phoenix_v4/libraries/micro_story_loader.py
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 PERSONA_FALLBACK
\f0\fs32 \cb7  maps personas to fallback personas when no atoms exist for the requested persona. Example:\
\

\f7 python\
PERSONA_FALLBACK = \{\
    "gen_z_la": ["gen_z_professionals", "gen_z"],\
    "gen_z": ["gen_z_professionals"],\
\}
\f0 \
\
If the story injector is built with 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 use_persona_fallback=True
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , it can use another persona\'92s atoms when the requested (persona, topic, role, \'85) has no files. That avoids assembly failure but is not a substitute for real coverage. Check where 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 MicroStoryLoader
\f0\fs32 \cb7  is instantiated (e.g. section_assembler, story_injector) to enable or disable fallback.\
\
### Option C: Restrict campaigns to ready pairs\
\
Run the prose QA (or any batch) only for (persona, topic) pairs that are **READY** in 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 story_atoms_coverage_report.py
\f0\fs32 \cb7  output, or that pass 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 check_topic_readiness.py ... --min-level RELEASE_READY
\f0\fs32 \cb7 . Then you don\'92t hit \'93No story_atoms found\'94 for those books.\
\
---\
\
## 4. Quick reference\
\
| Goal | Command / action |\
|------|-------------------|\
| Check one (topic, persona) | 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 python3 phoenix_v4/ci/check_topic_readiness.py <topic> <persona> --verbose
\f0\fs32 \cb7  |\
| Report all (persona, topic) | 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 python3 phoenix_v4/ci/story_atoms_coverage_report.py --out artifacts/story_atoms_coverage.json
\f0\fs32 \cb7  |\
| Add atoms | Create 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 story_atoms/\{persona\}/\{topic\}/\{engine\}/\{role\}/micro/*.txt
\f0\fs32 \cb7  (+ optional *_meta.yaml); engine in topic_engine_bindings |\
| Allow thin coverage in QA | Campaign with 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 --allow-coverage-gaps
\f0\fs32 \cb7  + 
\f7\fs28 \cb8 V4_QA_ALLOW_PROVISIONAL
\f0\fs32 \cb7  (assembly may still fail if no atoms at all for a slot) |\
